cs.NI, cs.WEB, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the performance challenges of HTTP/2 and its Server Push feature. 
- cs.WEB (Web Technologies) is also a likely category as the paper studies the impact of Server Push on real-world websites and proposes a novel strategy to improve its performance. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as HTTP/2 introduces new security challenges and the paper may discuss its implications. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as HTTP/2 is designed to improve the performance of distributed systems and the paper may discuss its impact on such systems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the software engineering challenges of implementing and optimizing Server Push.
